Unused method argument - `klass`. If it's necessary, use `_` or `_klass` as an argument name to indicate that it won't be used. You can also write as `test_assert_ancestor_method_names(*)` if you want the method to accept any arguments but don't care about them. (https://github.com/bbatsov/ruby-style-guide#underscore-unused-vars)

Unused method argument - `selection`. If it's necessary, use `_` or `_selection` as an argument name to indicate that it won't be used. You can also write as `test_assert_ancestor_method_names(*)` if you want the method to accept any arguments but don't care about them. (https://github.com/bbatsov/ruby-style-guide#underscore-unused-vars)
